<ns3539:section xmlns:ns3539="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" xml:id="resources.information.technologies.java.j2se.security.securitySupportLibraries.javaAuthenticationAndAuthorizationService">
    
    <ns3540:title xmlns:ns3540="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Java Authentication and Authorization Service (JAAS)</ns3540:title>

<ns3541:para xmlns:ns3541="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">This is a standard interface for authenticating persons or systems and
for  passing around secure user credentials and contexts. It enables one
to plug in different authentication technologies (<ns3542:abbrev xmlns:ns3542="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">e.g.</ns3542:abbrev> login screens, 
smart cards, Kerberos, public key infrastructure (PKI), ...).</ns3541:para>

<ns3543:para xmlns:ns3543="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">JAAS also provides a standard way for limiting access to resources based
on authenticated user identity.</ns3543:para>
    
</ns3539:section>